headline: Sysco (SYY) Is Up 9.7% After Raising FY26 EPS Guidance on Volume Gains and AI Push – Has The Bull Case Changed?
summary: Sysco Corporation recently reported fiscal 2026 second-quarter results, with sales rising to US$20,762 million while net income eased to US$389 million, and raised full-year adjusted EPS guidance to the high end of its prior range. Management pointed to improving case volumes across U.S. and international operations, expanding gross margins, disciplined expense control, and ongoing productivity initiatives, including its AI360 sales platform and tuck-in acquisitions, as key drivers of this...

headline: SYY Q4 Deep Dive: Productivity Initiatives and International Growth Drive Momentum
summary: Food distribution giant Sysco (NYSE:SYY) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 3% year on year to $20.76 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.99 per share was 1.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
